#!/usr/bin/env bash

cat tickets.txt

#!/bin/sh
set -x

touch tickets.txt

brew tap ankitpokhrel/jira-cli
brew install jira-cli

jira init --installation cloud --server https://makevisible.atlassian.net --login jirabot@makevisible.com --project VA --board "Visible Board"

# Use a for loop to iterate over the lines in the tickets.txt file
for in in $(cat tickets.txt); do
    # Check if jira command execution is successful
    if jira issue comment add "$in" "Build $PROJECT_BUILD_NUMBER" --no-input; then
        # Log the success message
        echo "Comment added to issue $in successfully"
    else
        # Log the error message
        echo "Failed to add comment to issue $in"
    fi

    # Sleep for a short amount of time to wait for the jira command to complete
    sleep 2
done

# Use a for loop to iterate over the lines in the tickets.txt file
for in in $(cat tickets.txt); do
    # Check if jira command execution is successful
    if jira issue move "$in" "Move to QA Backlog"; then
        # Log the success message
        echo "Issue $in moved successfully"
    else
        # Log the error message
        echo "Failed to move issue $in"
    fi

    # Sleep for a short amount of time to wait for the jira command to complete
    sleep 2
done
